						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab fixed in the left wall of the Aṅkēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Sōmēs11vara I]—A.D. 1048-49.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 970</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1048-49 A.D.,</hi> all other details of date, etc., being lost. It falls in the reign-period of Sōmēs11vara I who is perhaps the king mentioned in the beginning. It refers to a feudatory.</p>						

